00201560-0b7a-4a6c-8c0a-de09f5059786	Maslow Level: Physical Needs\n\nSub-Category: Sleep Deprivation and "Sleep Divorce"\n\nRelated Survey Variables: General Health / Daily Functioning\n\nPsychological Context: A spouse who snores severely, tosses and turns, or has vastly different sleep schedules can cause chronic sleep deprivation in their partner. Sleep is the ultimate Physical Need. A partner who hasn't slept properly in months will become irritable, resentful, and completely unable to engage in higher-level emotional or romantic connection.\n\nCounseling Framework & Diagnosis: The AI must treat this as a severe medical and logistical crisis, not a romantic failure. Society stigmatizes couples sleeping apart, but chronic sleep deprivation will destroy a marriage faster than separate bedrooms will.\n\nActionable Advice for the AI to Provide: 1. Remove the Stigma: Validate that sleeping in separate beds (a "sleep divorce") is a highly effective, healthy solution to protect the marriage's physical foundation. It does not mean the marriage is failing. 2. Medical Intervention: Strongly advise the snoring/disruptive partner to undergo a sleep study to rule out sleep apnea or other physical conditions. 3. Schedule Intimacy: If the couple chooses to sleep in separate rooms, they must proactively schedule times for physical affection and cuddling in the same bed before actually going to sleep.	{"source": "c:\\\\Users\\\\User\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\AI-Chatbot-for-Marriage-Counseling\\\\3-ai-service-python\\\\RAG_Knowledge_Base\\\\level1_physical_sleep_divorce.md"}	[0.030069435,0.026744036,-0.06579595,0.016756756,-0.043114435,-0.058349106,-0.009938057,-0.012298087,0.00096628716,0.060431927,0.0006115757,-0.013829479,0.046645988,-0.05087752,-0.01847722,-0.01987102,-0.033210907,-0.00032096493,-0.010295521,0.02087333,0.010875351,0.060909208,-0.023027495,0.024425719,-0.030268995,0.030102637,-0.020788886,-0.00043877907,0.034844447,0.034367934,-0.030548332,-0.05079