570d859b-3efa-439a-82a0-2c2532a19f08	Maslow Level: Safety Needs\n\nSub-Category: Future Security and Stability\n\nRelated Survey Variables: Pension / Retirement Security\n\nPsychological Context: Safety needs involve predictability, stability, and protection from future harm. The survey question regarding reliance on pension and social benefits in old age touches on a couple’s long-term financial safety net. A lack of agreement or confidence in this area creates existential dread about aging and abandonment.\n\nCounseling Framework & Diagnosis: Disagreements or fears about long-term security (like pensions) reveal a fracture in the marital safety net. Fear of the future often manifests in the present as controlling behaviors or extreme frugality.\n\nActionable Advice for the AI to Provide: 1. De-escalate Fear: Recognize that worries about old age and pensions are rooted in a deep human need for safety. 2. Proactive Planning: Encourage the couple to have a "Future Security" meeting. If they strongly disagree about their reliance on pensions, they must map out an alternative, concrete retirement plan. 3. Reassurance: Guide the partners to verbally assure each other that they will care for one another as they age, regardless of the financial outcome.	{"source": "c:\\\\Users\\\\User\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\AI-Chatbot-for-Marriage-Counseling\\\\3-ai-service-python\\\\RAG_Knowledge_Base\\\\level2_safety_needs.md"}	[0.03683651,0.003582611,-0.007529654,0.024491956,-0.005460318,-0.05919456,0.016519584,0.020422298,0.020228779,0.028318493,0.021568926,-0.042392824,0.02937079,-0.00033506504,0.0021486094,0.012099341,-0.031797282,0.012458146,0.007987073,0.03127947,0.028357988,-0.022646222,-0.034361426,-0.00962839,-0.08022496,0.0558548,-0.020517154,0.03599494,0.06986019,0.05451267,0.0037650976,-0.026072986,-0.009940516,-0.029391898,-0.035834122,-0.0043434096,0.0073565566,-0.04668803,-0.0008324046,-0.047999244,0.004193122,0.023671443,0.040795904,-0.031390592,-0.0783094