73867fc3-4740-452f-a944-112a40e16237	Maslow Level: Love and Belonging Needs\n\nSub-Category: Step-Parenting and Blended Families\n\nRelated Survey Variables: Number of Children / Family Structure\n\nPsychological Context: In blended families, biological bonds pre-date the marital bond. A step-parent often feels like an outsider in their own home, struggling to find "Belonging" when the biological parent and child have an established, impenetrable dynamic. Conflicts over discipline frequently tear the marriage apart.\n\nCounseling Framework & Diagnosis: If a user complains about their step-children's behavior, or feels their spouse always sides with the kids, the family lacks unified structural belonging. The adults are not functioning as a united front.\n\nActionable Advice for the AI to Provide: 1. Biological Parent Disciplines: Establish the golden rule of blended families: The biological parent must be the primary disciplinarian. The step-parent should focus on building a friendly relationship rather than acting as the enforcer. 2. The Unified Front: Advise the adults to discuss all parenting rules behind closed doors. They must present a completely united front to the children, never contradicting each other in public. 3. Prioritize the Marriage: Remind the couple that the children need the marriage to succeed to feel stable. They must schedule dedicated, child-free time to protect their romantic belonging.	{"source": "c:\\\\Users\\\\User\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\AI-Chatbot-for-Marriage-Counseling\\\\3-ai-service-python\\\\RAG_Knowledge_Base\\\\level3_love_blended_families.md"}	[-0.0025776292,-0.03602938,-0.01822964,0.019149054,-0.0065093725,-0.06499563,-0.013904304,0.025088832,0.0068539665,0.0027497686,-0.03129462,-0.002631355,0.0040571545,-0.027533693,-0.050039668,-0.012289965,-0.033951107,0.0070644915,-0.039264623,-0.018469831,0.011460127,0.0051578814,-0.04029749,0.030295515,0.015575781,0.045044333,0.008989349,0.013232052,0.0650531,-0.011060397,-