3a3aeba7-567d-4cd7-b34e-07e7bd820b11	Maslow Level: Love and Belonging Needs\n\nSub-Category: Mismatched Sex Drives\n\nRelated Survey Variables: MRQ (Romance, Attractiveness)\n\nPsychological Context: It is incredibly common for partners to have different levels of desire for physical intimacy. However, over time, the higher-drive partner feels chronically rejected and unloved, while the lower-drive partner feels objectified, pressured, and broken. This turns the bedroom into a battleground rather than a place of Belonging.\n\nCounseling Framework & Diagnosis: The AI must remain entirely neutral here. Neither partner is "wrong." The issue is not the frequency of sex, but the emotional meaning attached to the rejection and the pressure.\n\nActionable Advice for the AI to Provide: 1. De-couple Touch from Sex: Advise the couple to practice physical affection (cuddling, back rubs, holding hands) with a strict agreement that it will not lead to sex. This removes the lower-drive partner's anxiety and fulfills the higher-drive partner's need for touch. 2. Communicate Rejection Gently: Teach the lower-drive partner to reject the act, not the person. (e.g., "I love you and find you so attractive, but my body is too exhausted right now.") 3. Explore the "Brakes": Encourage the couple to discuss what "turns off" the lower-drive partner (stress, mess, feeling unheard) and work as a team to remove those obstacles, rather than just focusing on what "turns them on."	{"source": "c:\\\\Users\\\\User\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\AI-Chatbot-for-Marriage-Counseling\\\\3-ai-service-python\\\\RAG_Knowledge_Base\\\\level3_love_mismatched_libidos.md"}	[0.040704653,0.02495708,-0.016630547,0.012764655,-0.0084606,-0.06507562,0.0010340279,0.023425283,-0.019650731,-0.0014094963,-0.012343409,-0.011339033,-0.0027175492,-0.03677043,-0.042039264,-0.005837904,-0.010009881,-0.014628131,0.000910078,0.009708145,0.021857277,0.0139470585,-0.02419891,0.029299797,-0.03514456,0.05361047,0.002912559,