5e1631bc-1a85-432b-927b-f5301a0ba4df	Maslow Level: Love and Belonging Needs\n\nSub-Category: ADHD and Neurodivergence in Marriage\n\nRelated Survey Variables: Communication / Daily Functioning\n\nPsychological Context: When one partner has ADHD or is neurodivergent, standard communication advice often fails. The neurotypical partner may interpret forgetfulness, distraction, or hyper-fixation as a lack of love or respect (destroying Belonging). The neurodivergent partner often feels chronic shame and failure for not meeting standard marital expectations.\n\nCounseling Framework & Diagnosis: If a user complains that their spouse "never listens," "forgets everything I say," or acts like a distracted child, the AI must consider a neurological mismatch rather than malicious intent. The danger is the "Parent-Child" dynamic forming around daily chores.\n\nActionable Advice for the AI to Provide: 1. Separate Symptom from Intent: Advise the neurotypical partner to separate the neurological symptom (distraction) from the partner's intent (they still love you). Forgetfulness is not a personal betrayal. 2. Implement External Systems: Stop relying on memory. Advise the couple to use shared digital calendars, physical whiteboards, and visual reminders to manage household tasks. 3. Praise the Effort, Not Just the Outcome: Advise the couple to actively praise the neurodivergent partner's efforts to manage their symptoms, reducing the heavy burden of chronic shame.	{"source": "c:\\\\Users\\\\User\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\AI-Chatbot-for-Marriage-Counseling\\\\3-ai-service-python\\\\RAG_Knowledge_Base\\\\level3_love_neurodivergence.md"}	[0.006893412,-0.023757067,-0.034981336,0.02940083,-0.031918425,-0.07454137,-0.0040981458,-0.004926853,0.018538129,0.009741119,-0.035836264,-0.027649943,0.011671026,0.010735241,-0.027355742,-0.030549115,-0.057118185,-0.007886383,-0.033400536,-0.0133043,0.028011987,0.020631427,-0.056973193,0.031934757,-0.02464503,0.056672014,-0.0124427555,0.