4ad73e1e-0f5f-459c-b0a0-cbf3f7eec139	Maslow Level: Esteem Needs\n\nSub-Category: Career Inequality and Ambition Resentment\n\nRelated Survey Variables: GLOBE (Pride in individual accomplishments)\n\nPsychological Context: In modern marriages, a significant source of Esteem comes from professional and personal accomplishments. When one partner makes significantly more money, or views the other partner's career (or role as a stay-at-home parent) as "lesser," it creates a severe power imbalance.\n\nCounseling Framework & Diagnosis: If a user feels their ambitions are mocked, or if their domestic contributions are viewed as inferior to financial contributions, the foundation of mutual respect is broken.\n\nActionable Advice for the AI to Provide: 1. Equalize Value: The AI must emphasize that a healthy marriage assigns equal value to all contributions—whether financial, domestic, or emotional. Income does not dictate authority. 2. Active Cheerleading: Encourage the partners to actively ask about and celebrate each other's daily wins, no matter how small, to rebuild the habit of mutual pride. 3. Aligning Ambitions: Suggest a "state of the union" conversation where both partners discuss their individual 5-year goals and explicitly ask, "How can we structure our life so we both succeed?"	{"source": "c:\\\\Users\\\\User\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\AI-Chatbot-for-Marriage-Counseling\\\\3-ai-service-python\\\\RAG_Knowledge_Base\\\\level4_esteem_career_belittling.md"}	[0.01746486,-0.014680419,-0.019844355,0.01198524,-0.01870132,-0.039183944,0.00788387,0.010182351,0.0090703,-0.0101748435,-0.005145742,-0.020025184,0.030907998,-0.028068596,0.007069256,-0.017479585,-0.017515797,-0.017911185,-0.0058387355,-0.012997173,0.015113904,0.000995821,-0.050273735,0.02629535,-0.01817673,0.068202905,-0.015125477,0.022086406,0.052449416,0.020401437,-0.036284078,-0.007409096,-0.049390014,-0.029689198,-0.012780486,-0.050363258,-0.024729675,-0.029182304,-0.027085043,-0.059594758,0.004753