64ac85a1-99bd-4ab4-94e0-edaf6f510243	Maslow Level: Esteem Needs\n\nSub-Category: Phone Addiction and "Phubbing"\n\nRelated Survey Variables: MRQ (Enjoying company, Respect)\n\nPsychological Context: "Phubbing" (phone-snubbing) occurs when a partner constantly chooses their screen over engaging with their spouse. In the modern era, attention is the highest currency of respect. Giving priority to a phone over a partner's conversation sends a devastating Esteem signal: "This screen is more important than you."\n\nCounseling Framework & Diagnosis: If a user complains that their spouse is always on social media, texting, or playing games during dinner or in bed, they are expressing an Esteem injury. They feel invisible and devalued.\n\nActionable Advice for the AI to Provide: 1. Identify the Core Injury: Point out that scrolling while a partner is talking is not just a bad habit; it is a micro-rejection that kills emotional intimacy over time. 2. Create Tech-Free Zones: Advise the couple to agree on strict "no-screen" zones or times, such as the dinner table or the first 20 minutes in bed, to force intentional eye contact and conversation. 3. The 10-Minute Check-In: Suggest the couple implement a daily 10-minute check-in where phones are physically placed in another room, ensuring 100% undivided attention.	{"source": "c:\\\\Users\\\\User\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\AI-Chatbot-for-Marriage-Counseling\\\\3-ai-service-python\\\\RAG_Knowledge_Base\\\\level4_esteem_phubbing.md"}	[0.0041927625,-0.04098616,-0.018356424,0.093325496,-0.007664993,-0.028282978,0.007801141,-0.017086914,0.022215573,0.002643678,-0.008014402,-0.017891394,0.06367741,-0.0017808569,-0.040165197,-0.036691077,-0.02813664,0.0024764664,-0.019127218,-0.0012901144,0.022935797,0.024519643,-0.048379574,0.025386145,-0.050819382,0.042292286,-0.028143348,0.02341281,0.034229513,0.034249034,-0.015354823,0.021660006,-0.012196301,-0.015406987,-0.014017159,-0.059686515,0.0035011396,-0.015987583,-0.02575437,-0.0