165c577b-f217-4edb-ac09-ac850cccfa14	Maslow Level: Esteem Needs\n\nSub-Category: Stonewalling and Silent Treatment\n\nRelated Survey Variables: Communication / Respect\n\nPsychological Context: Stonewalling occurs when a partner completely shuts down, refuses to speak, or gives the "silent treatment" for days after a conflict. While it may stem from being emotionally overwhelmed, using silence to punish a partner is deeply disrespectful and attacks the partner's Esteem by making them feel invisible and worthless.\n\nCounseling Framework & Diagnosis: The AI must differentiate between a healthy "time-out" and toxic stonewalling. A time-out has a clear end time; stonewalling is indefinite emotional abandonment.\n\nActionable Advice for the AI to Provide: 1. Break the Silence: Advise the stonewalling partner that refusing to speak is destructive. They must learn to say, "I am too overwhelmed to talk right now, but I still love you, and we will talk tomorrow at 6 PM." 2. Self-Soothe: Encourage the stonewaller to practice self-soothing techniques (deep breathing, walking) during conflicts so they do not become so flooded that they shut down entirely. 3. Stop Chasing: Advise the partner receiving the silent treatment to stop "chasing" or begging for a response, as this feeds the power imbalance. They should state they are ready to talk when the partner is, and then focus on their own well-being.	{"source": "c:\\\\Users\\\\User\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\AI-Chatbot-for-Marriage-Counseling\\\\3-ai-service-python\\\\RAG_Knowledge_Base\\\\level4_esteem_stonewalling.md"}	[-0.011774649,0.0155845005,-0.044968784,0.06102859,-0.023834001,-0.04518552,-0.030168418,-0.01114271,-0.036994,0.029178467,-0.014212316,0.029772624,0.004877105,-0.027034711,-0.018531194,-0.023390962,-0.06935311,-0.036752444,-0.03239942,0.010787661,0.010795751,0.041951403,-0.00022709336,0.020364417,-0.014925532,0.036479466,-0.038316164,-4.5373845e-06,0.06606815,0.01947386,-0.03218329,-0.004790429,-0.0