e0bd0797-954a-4667-9dab-502f283d88a3	Maslow Level: Self-Actualization Needs\n\nSub-Category: Competing Visions (Career vs. Family)\n\nRelated Survey Variables: GLOBE (Cultural expectations) / Happiness\n\nPsychological Context: Self-actualization requires living in alignment with one's core values. A severe crisis occurs when partners realize they have fundamentally different visions for their lives—for example, one partner wants to sacrifice everything to build a business, while the other wants to prioritize a quiet family life and work-life balance.\n\nCounseling Framework & Diagnosis: This is not a petty argument; it is a clash of ultimate life goals. If a user feels their partner's career is destroying the family, or if a user feels their partner is holding them back from greatness, their Self-Actualization paths have diverged.\n\nActionable Advice for the AI to Provide: 1. Acknowledge the Divergence: Validate that it is painful when life visions shift. Neither vision (ambition vs. family focus) is inherently wrong, but the incompatibility is causing pain. 2. Seek the Compromise Anchor: Advise the couple to find the "anchor" they both agree on. Can the ambitious partner dedicate 100% to their career for 3 years, with a strict agreement to scale back afterward? 3. Define Success Together: Instruct the couple to explicitly define what a "successful life" looks like for them as a unit, ensuring that individual ambitions do not destroy the shared foundation.	{"source": "c:\\\\Users\\\\User\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\AI-Chatbot-for-Marriage-Counseling\\\\3-ai-service-python\\\\RAG_Knowledge_Base\\\\level5_actualization_career_vs_family.md"}	[0.008276745,-0.013187361,-0.013358229,-0.01694311,-0.014987647,-0.025278969,0.0025735116,0.0022083079,0.006517948,0.031809617,0.011217752,-0.05177665,0.032606054,-0.011767487,0.0045092553,0.002373038,-0.03659109,0.0062661166,-0.056438867,0.0018777021,0.032937232,0.019942041,-0.04112435,0.02342284,0.015928475,0.05876213