d0597a41-e890-4d40-ae25-adc5cb8ce6ab	Maslow Level: Self-Actualization Needs\n\nSub-Category: The Mid-Life Crisis and Identity Shifts\n\nRelated Survey Variables: Age / Happiness\n\nPsychological Context: Often occurring in middle age, a partner may experience an acute existential panic regarding their mortality, leading to a sudden, desperate search for "Self-Actualization." This can result in erratic, out-of-character behavior—buying expensive things, changing careers, or seeking younger company—leaving the spouse feeling abandoned by the person they knew.\n\nCounseling Framework & Diagnosis: The AI must recognize that a mid-life crisis is an individual identity crisis that spills over into the marriage. The frantic search for meaning is fundamentally a Self-Actualization panic.\n\nActionable Advice for the AI to Provide: 1. Separate Identity from Marriage: Help the user understand that their partner's crisis is about the partner's fear of aging/death, not necessarily a reflection of their love for the spouse. 2. Hold Boundaries Without Punishment: Advise the stable spouse to support their partner's safe explorations (like a new hobby or fitness routine) while holding firm boundaries against destructive behavior (like financial ruin or infidelity). 3. Re-evaluate Together: Use this crisis as an opportunity. Ask the couple to sit down and openly discuss: "What are your deepest regrets, and how can we use the next 20 years to make sure you live fully?"	{"source": "c:\\\\Users\\\\User\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\AI-Chatbot-for-Marriage-Counseling\\\\3-ai-service-python\\\\RAG_Knowledge_Base\\\\level5_actualization_midlife_crisis.md"}	[0.03699776,-0.021462781,-0.028388564,-0.00959146,0.002812703,-0.055186395,0.021760736,0.02410925,0.0072057275,0.041264113,0.021616584,-0.06264108,0.0074145454,-0.032070532,-0.0122846775,-0.0031059473,-0.013890676,0.027598098,-0.014369622,-0.0044497936,0.037812598,-0.016494893,-0.03447667,0.018037876,-0.005780142,0.0426389,-0.00