f44bcbcd-0532-47d3-a398-6d78342b8dc4	Maslow Level: Self-Actualization Needs\n\nSub-Category: Meaning, Happiness, and Spiritual Alignment\n\nRelated Survey Variables: MRQ (Are you happy?), Religiosity (Are you religious?)\n\nPsychological Context: Self-actualization is the pinnacle of the hierarchy, representing personal growth, profound happiness, and shared meaning (often expressed through shared values or religiosity). If lower-level needs are met but a partner still feels unfulfilled, it is a crisis of meaning. Differences in religious intensity (religiosity) can also fracture a couple's shared vision of life.\n\nCounseling Framework & Diagnosis: When basic marital functioning is fine but "happiness" is absent, or if differing religious values cause conflict, the couple is struggling to self-actualize together. They lack a shared purpose or spiritual alignment.\n\nActionable Advice for the AI to Provide: 1. Finding Shared Meaning: If happiness is low, advise the couple to explore what gives their life purpose outside of daily chores. Suggest volunteering, taking up a meaningful shared hobby, or setting life goals together. 2. Navigating Religious Differences: If differing religiosity is a pain point, advise the couple to focus on shared core values (like kindness, charity, or family) rather than theological differences. Teach them to support each other's spiritual or personal growth journeys without demanding conformity. 3. Individual Growth: Remind the user that a healthy marriage supports the individual self-actualization of both partners. Encourage them to ask their spouse: "How can I support your personal dreams this year?"	{"source": "c:\\\\Users\\\\User\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\AI-Chatbot-for-Marriage-Counseling\\\\3-ai-service-python\\\\RAG_Knowledge_Base\\\\level5_self_actualization.md"}	[0.019500095,-0.025032174,-0.033243127,0.012254942,-0.020116054,-0.051950805,0.025709143,0.020319374,-0.0126229515,0.017692352,-0.0016403317,-0.020988615,-0.