COPY public.faq (id, question, answer) FROM stdin;
1	How do I start a new session?	You can start a new session by navigating to the Home page and typing in the chat box at the bottom. The AI will automatically begin responding.
2	Is my data private?	Yes. All your conversations and check-in data are securely stored and strictly private. We do not share your information with any third parties.
3	How is my relationship risk calculated?	Our AI model analyzes your daily check-ins, the severity of unmet needs based on Maslow's hierarchy, and long-term behavioral trends to provide a reliable risk baseline.
4	Can I export my chat history?	Yes. You can navigate to Settings > Privacy & Security and click on the 'Export' button to download a copy of your session data.
5	How does the system determine my marital risk score?	The marital risk score is calculated using clinical psychometric models (such as the Marital Satisfaction Scale) based on your initial registration assessment regarding trust, emotional safety, and communication. The AI continuously updates this baseline based on your daily check-ins.
\.
;

